{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1778305442,"nonce":"JReKc63+qLHGTbnuWU4o10CHrPo=","title":"Pre-registered run: 3-cell anti-anticipation matrix on baseline GRU (jerk x motor-pre-go x full-smooth-high)","message":"## Pre-registration\n\nFiled BEFORE running. Hypothesis, predictions, and decision criteria are committed in advance.\n\n## Hypothesis (primary)\n\nSuppressing pre-go-cue anticipation (currently 5.4-7.6 mm goal-directed drift in 200 ms pre-go window across all GRU replicates of the prior 2x2x2 baseline matrix) will reduce within-condition pairwise RMSE on post-go forward-velocity profiles, beating the prior winner GRU/jerk's 0.76 variance ratio.\n\n## Hypothesis (mechanistic)\n\nPre-go drift indicates a soft state-space boundary at the go-cue. Replicates land in different basins under the jerk penalty (peak-velocity bimodality, see efc4d68 comments). A hard hold/move boundary, enforced via either pre-go motor-output mask (strategy 1) or strong full-trajectory smoothness (strategy 3, literature-aligned), should reduce basin-selection variance globally.\n\n## Cells\n\nAll cells share: GRU architecture, jerk weight 1e5, baseline (no adversary), 12000 warmup batches, batch size 250, 5 replicates, n_steps adjusted for new task structure (~140-150).\n\nTask config (CHANGED): `epoch_len_ranges = [[0, 1], [10, 30]]` — pure-hold collapsed to 0 steps; target-on now 100-300 ms (matches Shahbazi 2025 §4.2). Movement window unchanged.\n\n| # | Run label                            | Anti-anticipation lever |\n|---|--------------------------------------|-------------------------|\n| 1 | `gru__jerk`                          | none (control, new task only) |\n| 2 | `gru__jerk_motor_pre`                | `--nn-output-pre-go 1e-2` (strategy 1) |\n| 3 | `gru__jerk_smooth_high`              | `--nn-hidden-derivative 1e2` (strategy 3, full-trajectory, Shahbazi-aligned) |\n\n## Decision criteria (committed BEFORE the run)\n\nThree measurements per cell:\n\n(A) Within-cell pairwise RMSE on post-go forward velocity (mean ± SD across all C(5,2) = 10 pairs).\n(B) Pre-go drift: signed forward velocity in the [-200 ms, 0 ms] window relative to go-cue (per replicate, mean over 8 directions). Reported as mm of motion.\n(C) Variance ratio: within-cell RMSE / minimum across-cell RMSE.\n\nPass criteria for the run to be informative:\n\n- All 3 cells must converge (final training loss \u003c 5.0 for GRU; if any cell has loss \u003e 7.0 in any rep we re-run with longer warmup before drawing conclusions).\n- Within-cell RMSE for at least one cell must be \u003c 0.10 m/s (the prior best was 0.112 from GRU/jerk).\n- For cells (2) and (3): pre-go drift should drop to \u003c 1 mm if the strategy worked, vs the 5.4-7.6 mm baseline.\n\nPredicted outcomes (committed in advance):\n\n- Cell (1) `gru__jerk`: drift ~5-7 mm (similar to prior matrix); within-cell RMSE ~0.10-0.13 m/s.\n- Cell (2) `gru__jerk_motor_pre`: drift \u003c 1 mm; within-cell RMSE \u003c 0.08 m/s if soft-boundary hypothesis is right; ~0.10 if mostly orthogonal.\n- Cell (3) `gru__jerk_smooth_high`: drift \u003c 1 mm but post-go peak likely lower (smoothness penalty dampens reach dynamics); within-cell RMSE somewhere between (1) and (2).\n\nIf cells (2) AND (3) both achieve drift \u003c 1 mm but neither gets within-cell RMSE \u003c 0.05, the soft-boundary hypothesis is plausibly disproved at the variance level — the basin-selection issue would be independent of anticipation, and we'd escalate to other strategies (activity L2 sweep, vRNN tau-sweep, etc.).\n\nIf cell (2) achieves both drift \u003c 1 mm AND within-cell RMSE \u003c 0.05, adopt as new default and resume the original chain of work (umbrella f695729).\n\nIf cell (3) wins, adopt the literature-aligned (full-trajectory smoothness 1e2) approach as default — simpler, no masking infrastructure needed in production runs.\n\n## Cross-references\n\n- Anti-anticipation issue: 5acdaae (5-strategy menu)\n- Smoothness retrain umbrella: efc4d68\n- Phase umbrella: f695729 (Stage 0 closed; this gates resumption of Stages 1+)\n- Subagent findings driving this: anticipation_motornet_v3.md, peak_velocity_diagnostic.md, variance_matrix_results.md\n\n## Resolution\n\nWhen the run completes: a comment on this issue with measured (A), (B), (C) per cell. The pre-reg becomes the basis for RESULTS.md per the CLAUDE.md post-training-run protocol.","files":null}]}